    "_postman_id": "11895b3b-4e37-46c3-a771-7d15cbf602db",
    "name": "WhatsApp Organizations API Copy 3",
    "description": "Multi-organization WhatsApp service (Express + MongoDB).\n\n**Dynamic updates (no Postman re-import)**\n1. **REST Client / Cursor:** open `postman/WhatsApp-Organizations-API.http` in the editor — requests always match the file on disk; edit `@variables` at the top.\n2. **CLI:** `npm install` then `npm run postman:run` — Newman reads the JSON files from disk every time.\n3. **Postman app:** still requires re-import when the JSON changes (Postman limitation).\n\n**Updating the Postman collection file**\nIf you use the Postman GUI: **Import** → replace collection when `WhatsApp-Organizations-API.postman_collection.json` changes; re-import `WhatsApp-Organizations-API.postman_environment.json` for env vars.\n\n**Before first request**\n1. Import this collection **and** `WhatsApp-Organizations-API.postman_environment.json`, then select environment **Local (WhatsApp API)**.\n2. Or: Collection → **Variables** → set `adminKey` to the **exact** same string as `ADMIN_API_KEY` in your server `.env` (default in `.env.example` is `change-me-long-random-secret`).\n3. If you see `Invalid or missing admin key`, `adminKey` in Postman does not match `ADMIN_API_KEY` on the server — fix one or the other so they are identical.\n\n**Variables**\n- `baseUrl` — local dev, e.g. `http://localhost:3000`\n- `deployedBaseUrl` — **public** https origin where Meta sends webhooks (must match Meta Callback URL host). Use this for **GET Webhook logs (deployed)** so you read logs from the same server Meta hits.\n- `adminKey` — must equal server `ADMIN_API_KEY` (organization provisioning + webhook debug logs)\n- `organizationId` — from **POST Create organization** response `id`\n- `apiKey` — from create response (for `/api/*`)\n- `webhookApiKey` — same as `apiKey`\n- `leadId` — for PATCH lead\n- `webhookLogLimit` — max entries for **GET Webhook logs** (default `100`)\n- `templateTestPhone` — digits-only WhatsApp recipient for **POST Send template — pre_trevel** (include country code, no `+`)\n- `preTrevelTemplateName` — usually `pre_trevel` (must match Meta template name exactly)\n- `preTrevelLanguageCode` — usually `en` (must match approved template language)\n\n**Auth**\n- Org routes and **Webhook debug logs** use **Bearer Token** `{{adminKey}}` (or header `X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}`).\n- Other API routes use header **x-api-key:** `{{apiKey}}`.\n\n**Meta webhook URL:** `{{baseUrl}}/webhook/{{webhookApiKey}}`\n\n**Templates:** `GET {{baseUrl}}/api/templates` lists templates (WABA). `POST {{baseUrl}}/api/templates/send` sends a template message via Meta `POST /{phone-number-id}/messages` (`type: template`) using `phoneNumberId` + `accessToken`.\n\n**Inbound debugging:** After messages hit your server, open **GET Webhook logs (raw)** — each entry includes `raw` (full Meta JSON string). In-memory only; restart clears. Optional env `WEBHOOK_LOG_MAX` caps buffer size.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "27146035",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/27146035-11895b3b-4e37-46c3-a771-7d15cbf602db?source=collection_link"
  },
