    {
      "name": "Organizations (X-Admin-Key)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Create organization",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let data = {};",
                  "try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                  "if (data.id) pm.environment.set('organizationId', data.id);",
                  "if (data.apiKey) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('apiKey', data.apiKey);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('webhookApiKey', data.apiKey);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{adminKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"businessName\": \"Acme Corp\",\n  \"businessType\": \"retail\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/organizations",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "organizations"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Creates an organization and returns `apiKey`. Copy `id` → variable `organizationId`, `apiKey` → `apiKey` and `webhookApiKey`.\n\nUses Bearer token = `adminKey` (same value as `ADMIN_API_KEY` in server `.env`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH Set WhatsApp credentials",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let body = {};",
                  "try { body = JSON.parse(pm.request.body.raw || '{}'); } catch (e) {}",
                  "if (body.verifyToken) pm.environment.set('webhookVerifyToken', body.verifyToken);",
                  "if (body.phoneNumberId) pm.environment.set('phoneNumberId', body.phoneNumberId);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{adminKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"businessAccountId\": \"YOUR_WABA_ID\",\n  \"phoneNumberId\": \"YOUR_PHONE_NUMBER_ID\",\n  \"accessToken\": \"YOUR_LONG_LIVED_TOKEN\",\n  \"verifyToken\": \"YOUR_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN\",\n  \"number\": \"+15551234567\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/organizations/{{organizationId}}/whatsapp",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "organizations",
                "{{organizationId}}",
                "whatsapp"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sets Meta WhatsApp credentials. Required fields: `businessAccountId`, `phoneNumberId`, `accessToken`, `verifyToken`. Set variable `organizationId` to the `id` from create response. Bearer token = `adminKey` (must match server `ADMIN_API_KEY`)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Webhook debug logs (X-Admin-Key)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Webhook logs (raw)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{adminKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/webhook-logs?all=true",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "webhook-logs"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "all",
                  "value": "true"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Reads logs from **this** `baseUrl` process only (e.g. localhost).\n\nReturns Meta webhook traffic from **in-memory** buffer (newest first).\n\n**Multi-tenant:** Default returns **all organizations** in this process. Each log includes `organizationId`, `businessName`, `phoneNumberId` (from DB when the path apiKey matched an org), plus `apiKey` from the URL path.\n\n**Response:** `count`, `max`, `returned`, `limitRequested`, `filter` (null or `{ organizationId, apiKey }`), `logs[]`, `diagnostic`. Each log: `id`, `receivedAt`, `method`, `path`, `organizationId`, `businessName`, `phoneNumberId`, `apiKey`, `headers`, `raw`, `kind`, `outcome`, `httpStatus`.\n\n**Query:** `all=true` — return up to `WEBHOOK_LOG_MAX` entries (full buffer). `limit` — cap (1–2000) when `all` is not set. `organizationId` — filter to one org. `apiKey` — filter to one org’s `wk_…` key.\n\n**Outcomes:** `ok` | `unknown_org` | `invalid_signature` | `missing_api_key_in_url` | `error`.\n\n**Auth:** Bearer = `adminKey`.\n\n**Note:** Per-process buffer; restart clears. Set `WEBHOOK_LOG_MAX` in `.env` for capacity.\n\n**If Meta uses a public domain:** use **GET Webhook logs (deployed / Meta host)** instead."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Webhook logs (deployed / Meta host)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{adminKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{deployedBaseUrl}}/api/webhook-logs?all=true&limit={{webhookLogLimit}}",
              "host": [
                "{{deployedBaseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "webhook-logs"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "all",
                  "value": "true"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "{{webhookLogLimit}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "**Use this when Meta Callback URL is on a public host** (e.g. `https://whatsapp.instabus.co.in/webhook/wk_...`).\n\nMeta POSTs there; in-memory logs live on **that** Node process. You must call `/api/webhook-logs` on the **same** `https://` origin — not `localhost`.\n\nSet environment variable `deployedBaseUrl` to your public origin (no trailing slash). Set `adminKey` to the **production** `ADMIN_API_KEY` (same as on the deployed server).\n\nSame response shape as **GET Webhook logs (raw)**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "DELETE Clear webhook logs",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{adminKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/webhook-logs",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "webhook-logs"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Clears the in-memory webhook debug buffer.\n\n**Auth:** Bearer = `adminKey`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
