                    "{{baseUrl}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "api",
                    "templates"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Returns WhatsApp message templates for this organization’s **WhatsApp Business Account** by calling Meta Graph API `GET /{whatsapp-business-account-id}/message_templates` with the org’s stored `businessAccountId` and `accessToken`.\n\n**Auth:** `x-api-key` = organization `apiKey`.\n\n**Prerequisites:** `PATCH /api/organizations/:id/whatsapp` must include `businessAccountId` (WABA id) and `accessToken` with `whatsapp_business_management` (and template read) permissions.\n\n**Response:** `data` — array of template objects (Meta shape); `paging` — cursor pagination when present.\n\n**Optional query (passed to Meta):** `limit` (1–1000), `after`, `before` (cursors), `name` (filter by template name), `status` (e.g. `APPROVED`, `PENDING`), `fields` (comma-separated field list).\n\n**Errors:** `503` if WABA/token not set; `4xx/5xx` from Meta with `metaError` detail; `502` for network/other failures.\n\nMeta docs: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/whats-app-business-account/message_templates"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "POST Send template — pre_trevel (utility)",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "type": "text/javascript",
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test('Status is 201', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                      "var j = {}; try { j = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                      "pm.test('Response has ok and metaMessageId', function () {",
                      "  pm.expect(j.ok).to.eql(true);",
                      "  pm.expect(j.metaMessageId).to.be.a('string');",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test('debug: metaPayload matches template send shape', function () {",
                      "  if (!j.metaPayload) return;",
                      "  pm.expect(j.metaPayload.type).to.eql('template');",
                      "  pm.expect(j.metaPayload.template.name).to.eql(j.templateName);",
                      "  var c = j.metaPayload.template.components || [];",
                      "  pm.expect(c.length).to.be.at.least(2);",
                      "  pm.expect(c[0].type).to.eql('header');",
                      "  pm.expect(c[1].type).to.eql('body');",
                      "});"
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  },
                  {
                    "key": "x-api-key",
                    "value": "{{apiKey}}"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"to\": \"{{templateTestPhone}}\",\n  \"templateName\": \"{{preTrevelTemplateName}}\",\n  \"languageCode\": \"{{preTrevelLanguageCode}}\",\n  \"headerParameters\": [\n    \"ABC\"\n  ],\n  \"bodyParameters\": [\n    \"Radha krishna\",\n    \"10:00am\",\n    \"Delhi\"\n  ],\n  \"debug\": true\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/templates/send",
                  "host": [
                    "{{baseUrl}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "api",
                    "templates",
                    "send"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "**Ready-to-test `pre_trevel` utility template** (one HEADER text variable + three BODY text variables + quick-reply buttons — buttons need no payload).\n\n### Before you send\n1. **Create org** + **PATCH WhatsApp** with real `phoneNumberId`, `accessToken`, `businessAccountId`.\n2. Set **`apiKey`** (and optionally **`templateTestPhone`**) in the environment or collection variables.\n3. Confirm template name and language: run **GET List message templates** and find `pre_trevel` — use exact `name` and `language` (e.g. `en`). Update `preTrevelTemplateName` / `preTrevelLanguageCode` if different.\n4. Recipient must have **opted in**; for dev, add the number in Meta **To** list.\n\n### Body fields\n- `headerParameters`: one string → maps to the HEADER text variable\n- `bodyParameters`: three strings in order → passenger name, departure time, boarding point\n\n### Debug\nWith `\"debug\": true` (or `?debug=true`), the **201** response includes **`metaPayload`**: the exact JSON sent to Meta (no token). Remove `debug` in production if you prefer a smaller response.\n\n**Success:** `201` with `metaMessageId`. **Errors:** `502` + `metaError` (see `metaPayload` when `debug` is on).\n\nMeta: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/guides/send-messages#template-messages"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
